00:00:16.040 --> 00:00:21.600
data science community to connect and chat about data science leadership, questions you're

00:00:21.600 --> 00:00:26.920
facing and what's going on in the world of data science. So these sessions are recorded

00:00:26.920 --> 00:00:33.240
and shared to the RStudio YouTube, as well as the RStudio Data Science Hangout site.

00:00:33.240 --> 00:00:39.040
Try to get them up at least a week after each session. So you can always go back and rewatch

00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:44.360
or find helpful resources. We also have a LinkedIn group for the Hangout, too. So if

00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:48.939
you ever want to continue a certain discussion, or if anybody wants to talk to each other

00:00:48.939 --> 00:00:55.320
in there, other than me just talking in there, please feel free to join that group. And Tyler

00:00:55.480 --> 00:01:01.119
or Hannah will share it in a second in the chat. Together, we're all dedicated to creating

00:01:01.119 --> 00:01:06.800
a welcoming environment for everybody here. So we love when everyone can participate and

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:11.800
we can hear from everybody. So there's three ways that you can ask questions today. You

00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:17.959
can jump in by raising your hand on Zoom. You can put questions in the Zoom chat. Feel

00:01:17.959 --> 00:01:22.559
free to put a little star next to it if you want me to read it, or I can call on you to

00:01:22.559 --> 00:01:28.639
introduce yourselves and add some context, too. Lastly, we also have a Slido link where

00:01:28.639 --> 00:01:35.720
you can ask questions anonymously. And Hannah will share that in the chat as well. I just

00:01:35.720 --> 00:01:39.440
want to reiterate before we get started that we love to hear from everybody, no matter

00:01:39.440 --> 00:01:47.519
your level of experience or area of work, too. And today, I am so excited to be joined

00:01:47.519 --> 00:01:54.279
by my co-host for the day, Maitili Krishnaraj, Global Delivery Lead, Pricing and Analytics

00:01:54.279 --> 00:02:01.080
Platform at AXA Excel. And Maitili, I would love to have you just start by introducing

00:02:01.080 --> 00:02:06.639
yourself and telling us a little bit about your role, the company, and maybe also something

00:02:06.639 --> 00:02:09.479
you like to do in your free time outside of work.

00:02:09.479 --> 00:02:16.679
Sure, sure. Thank you, Rachel. That's quite a warm welcome. And it's nice to be here because

00:02:16.839 --> 00:02:23.440
being, you know, a customer on the other side of our studio, and I keep telling this to

00:02:23.440 --> 00:02:29.479
everyone, that it's become a product which I started loving so much. So I'm glad to be

